n within contemporary debates on Ireland’s present and future. This book is concerned with its role in the modernisation of Ireland. In so doing it also addresses topics of continued relevance for the Ireland of today, including the Northern Ireland Peace Process and the institutional care of children.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aPolitical participationzIrelandxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Ireland.2bisacsh  aCatholic Church.  aDebate.  aIdeas.  aInfluence.  aPolicy.  aPolitical parties.1 aFinn, Tomás, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526130136423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526130136/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles